00:01:00,212 --> 00:01:02,842
(Electricity Bill, Jung Hee Wan)

10
00:01:04,555 --> 00:01:05,955
You died that day.

11
00:01:07,185 --> 00:01:08,255
Four years ago.

12
00:01:09,225 --> 00:01:10,225
Yes.

13
00:01:11,455 --> 00:01:13,765
But I came because I had to say something.

14
00:01:14,065 --> 00:01:15,065
Kim Ram Woo.

15
00:01:17,295 --> 00:01:19,465
You will die a week from now.

16
00:01:21,365 --> 00:01:22,405
What?

17
00:01:22,535 --> 00:01:26,075
You will die 176 hours 12 minutes and 35 seconds later.

18
00:01:26,645 --> 00:01:28,945
I will die? Next week?

19
00:01:29,345 --> 00:01:30,415
Yes.

20
00:01:30,675 --> 00:01:32,015
How do you know that?

21
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:33,615
Are you a grim reaper?

22
00:01:33,845 --> 00:01:34,885
Yes.

23
00:02:14,585 --> 00:02:16,425
I'll leave it by the door, then.

24
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:19,664
- Hey, mister. Wait. - What for?

25
00:02:19,665 --> 00:02:21,925
Can you help me? A weirdo's in my house.

26
00:02:22,295 --> 00:02:23,295
What?

27
00:02:23,395 --> 00:02:25,635
- Call the police, then. - Well...

28
00:02:26,365 --> 00:02:28,065
- What can a courier do? - Thanks.

29
00:02:30,575 --> 00:02:31,605
Watch out.

30
00:02:36,445 --> 00:02:37,745
Is he hiding in the bathroom?

31
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:40,284
He's standing right in front of you.

32
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:42,515
- Where? - This guy right here.

33
00:02:42,955 --> 00:02:43,955
What?

34
00:02:44,585 --> 00:02:46,924
There is no guy right here.

35
00:02:46,925 --> 00:02:49,595
He can't see me, so don't waste your time.

36
00:02:50,225 --> 00:02:53,095
My gosh. He has so long left to live.

37
00:02:53,925 --> 00:02:55,995
Good for you. You'll live to be very old.

38
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:57,395
- You don't hear that? - What?

39
00:02:57,695 --> 00:02:58,795
Hear what?

40
00:03:05,535 --> 00:03:07,205
- I'm dead busy. - You won't die.

41
00:03:07,305 --> 00:03:08,605
Well, the thing is...

42
00:03:08,975 --> 00:03:11,245
- I'm sorry, but... - Forget it.

43
00:03:11,275 --> 00:03:13,115
Does she think I'm someone who runs errands?

44
00:03:13,145 --> 00:03:14,185
Sorry.

45
00:03:15,685 --> 00:03:18,254
Hello? Can I talk to the doctor?

46
00:03:18,255 --> 00:03:19,455
I'm Jung Hee Wan.

47
00:03:19,855 --> 00:03:21,225
It's really urgent.

48
00:03:21,255 --> 00:03:23,324
The medicine I was prescribed.

49
00:03:23,325 --> 00:03:25,425
Do any of them cause hallucinations?

50
00:03:25,795 --> 00:03:26,925
They do, right?

51
00:03:27,195 --> 00:03:29,634
Did you check every single medication...

52
00:03:29,635 --> 00:03:30,635
Yes.

53
00:03:30,636 --> 00:03:33,935
The average person needs 2 to 3 hours to come around.

54
00:03:35,805 --> 00:03:39,005
Later on, you'll look back and regret wasting time doing this.

55
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:41,405
You'll have so many regrets once you die.

56
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,215
If you need advice on...

57
00:03:53,855 --> 00:03:54,855
Excuse me.

58
00:03:54,856 --> 00:03:55,925
(Buddhist text)

59
00:03:56,025 --> 00:03:57,154
Excuse me?

60
00:03:57,155 --> 00:03:58,295
(Buddhist text)

61
00:03:58,595 --> 00:03:59,725
I have...

62
00:04:00,095 --> 00:04:01,824
a few years of experience,

63
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:04,665
so stuff like this is nothing but background noise.

64
00:04:08,205 --> 00:04:09,705
Have you come around?

65
00:04:10,835 --> 00:04:13,205
Then let's do some cleaning up.

66
00:04:14,145 --> 00:04:15,844
Look at all this food.

67
00:04:15,845 --> 00:04:17,315
You haven't touched a thing.

68
00:04:17,615 --> 00:04:19,814
How heartbroken would your dad and Hee Ju be...

69
00:04:19,815 --> 00:04:21,185
if they saw this after you died?

70
00:04:23,215 --> 00:04:24,285
Who are you?

71
00:04:25,485 --> 00:04:27,225
What? I'm Hee Wan.

72
00:04:27,425 --> 00:04:28,825
Cut the crap.

73
00:04:28,885 --> 00:04:31,194
If you say my name once more, I'll beat you up.

74
00:04:31,195 --> 00:04:32,854
I'm Jung Hee Wan.

75
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:34,264
You're Kim Ram Woo.

76
00:04:34,265 --> 00:04:35,265
I don't believe this.

77
00:04:35,266 --> 00:04:38,835
You're the one who insisted we swap names.

78
00:04:44,735 --> 00:04:45,935
Our yearbook.

79
00:04:47,405 --> 00:04:51,315
Don't you remember using stickers to correct our names?

80
00:04:51,575 --> 00:04:53,185
We had to stay back for a month to clean the school.

81
00:04:53,645 --> 00:04:54,785
Here you are.

82
00:04:55,415 --> 00:04:57,815
All the trouble I went to stick...

83
00:04:58,085 --> 00:04:59,615
(Kim Ram Woo)

84
00:05:02,425 --> 00:05:03,425
Kim Ram Woo.

85
00:05:04,155 --> 00:05:05,195
What?

86
00:05:14,935 --> 00:05:16,775
Salt. Chicken blood.

87
00:05:17,635 --> 00:05:19,535
I was assaulted with everything.

88
00:05:24,045 --> 00:05:25,175
A fire extinguisher.

89
00:05:26,275 --> 00:05:27,445
That's new.

90
00:05:29,885 --> 00:05:31,015
Kim Ram Woo.

91
00:05:31,955 --> 00:05:32,955
What?

92
00:05:32,956 --> 00:05:34,585
Do you know Bang Ji Su?

93
00:05:34,725 --> 00:05:36,495
- Who? - Tenth-grader Bang Ji Su.

94
00:05:37,095 --> 00:05:38,255
She's looking for you.

95
00:05:39,825 --> 00:05:41,825
The hair product commercial girl.

96
00:05:44,535 --> 00:05:46,035
Oh, her.

97
00:05:50,005 --> 00:05:53,645
I have dreadful handwriting.

98
00:05:53,905 --> 00:05:56,944
I saw the letter you wrote for my friend.

99
00:05:56,945 --> 00:05:59,785
It was so nice and pretty.

100
00:06:00,345 --> 00:06:02,215
I see word spread far and wide.

101
00:06:02,715 --> 00:06:04,084
Is it a love letter?

102
00:06:04,085 --> 00:06:07,185
There are four prices, each for the basic,

103
00:06:07,385 --> 00:06:09,955
premium, special, or platinum design.

104
00:06:10,025 --> 00:06:11,095
Platinum, please.

105
00:06:11,255 --> 00:06:13,494
That's a bit expensive.

106
00:06:13,495 --> 00:06:14,495
That's fine.

107
00:06:14,595 --> 00:06:15,765
It's 30 dollars.

108
00:06:15,965 --> 00:06:16,965
That's fine.

109
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:21,064
Can I have it next week?

110
00:06:21,065 --> 00:06:23,405
That's when I'm going to say I like him.

111
00:06:23,535 --> 00:06:24,634
If we start dating then,

112
00:06:24,635 --> 00:06:27,145
Christmas will be our 100th day together.

113
00:06:27,805 --> 00:06:30,245
Him rejecting your proposal...

114
00:06:30,475 --> 00:06:31,744
isn't an option for you?

115
00:06:31,745 --> 00:06:33,584
Well...

116
00:06:33,585 --> 00:06:34,645
No.

117
00:06:35,815 --> 00:06:38,015
- Here's the letter. - Okay.

118
00:06:40,355 --> 00:06:42,284
"Your dizzying good looks,"

119
00:06:42,285 --> 00:06:43,855
"your smile that makes my heart race."

120
00:06:44,595 --> 00:06:46,595
There's someone this handsome at our school?

121
00:06:46,965 --> 00:06:48,425
"I don't usually approach..."

122
00:06:50,965 --> 00:06:52,335
"Just you, Ram Woo?"

123
00:06:52,835 --> 00:06:53,835
Yes.

124
00:06:54,365 --> 00:06:55,665
Kim Ram Woo.

125
00:06:56,975 --> 00:06:58,034
Not you.

126
00:06:58,035 --> 00:07:00,705
Kim Ram Woo who goes by Jung Hee Wan.

127
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:03,945
This letter is for Kim Ram Woo?

128
00:07:04,015 --> 00:07:05,245
The Kim Ram Woo I know?

129
00:07:05,275 --> 00:07:06,585
Yes. Why?

130
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:08,715
Is that a problem?

131
00:07:09,985 --> 00:07:12,415
No, there's no problem.

132
00:07:12,715 --> 00:07:14,684
I'm just not sure...

133
00:07:14,685 --> 00:07:17,755
if Ram Woo likes stuff like this.

134
00:07:18,195 --> 00:07:19,255
Does he not?

135
00:07:19,655 --> 00:07:21,664
Should I skip the whole letter thing...

136
00:07:21,665 --> 00:07:23,365
and ask him out to his face?

137
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:27,465
No, don't do that. A letter's fine.

138
00:07:27,565 --> 00:07:29,465
A letter would be perfect.

139
00:07:29,505 --> 00:07:32,405
Written words get the message across with more meaning.

140
00:07:32,505 --> 00:07:33,505
It's perfect.

141
00:07:33,506 --> 00:07:34,675
Okay, then.

142
00:07:35,405 --> 00:07:36,615
Then here is...

143
00:07:37,275 --> 00:07:38,345
your 30 dollars.

144
00:07:42,285 --> 00:07:43,285
Wait!

145
00:07:45,085 --> 00:07:46,985
Yes? What is it?

146
00:07:50,895 --> 00:07:55,024
You can choose from modern, classic, petit, or lovely.

147
00:07:55,025 --> 00:07:56,125
What do you want?

148
00:07:57,935 --> 00:08:00,434
Since you're closest to Ram Woo,

149
00:08:00,435 --> 00:08:02,865
pick whatever theme you think he'll like.

150
00:08:02,965 --> 00:08:03,975
Good luck.

151
00:08:05,205 --> 00:08:06,235
Good luck.

152
00:08:08,675 --> 00:08:10,644
(My dear Ram Woo)

153
00:08:10,645 --> 00:08:12,644
"Your dizzying good looks?"

154
00:08:12,645 --> 00:08:16,144
You stay up every night thinking of him too?

155
00:08:16,145 --> 00:08:17,985
Quit drinking coffee, then.

156
00:08:26,425 --> 00:08:27,525
Darn it.

157
00:08:28,725 --> 00:08:30,134
It's so annoying.

158
00:08:30,135 --> 00:08:32,335
(18th, Bang Ji Su's D-day)

159
00:08:38,405 --> 00:08:39,405
Kim Ram Woo.

160
00:08:45,315 --> 00:08:47,145
What's up with you? Are you a zombie?

161
00:08:48,015 --> 00:08:49,015
What?

162
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:50,785
She's outside.

163
00:08:51,855 --> 00:08:53,455
Bang Ji Su?

164
00:08:55,055 --> 00:08:57,324
Just write out what she asked.

165
00:08:57,325 --> 00:08:58,325
No.

166
00:08:58,825 --> 00:09:01,464
Tell her I'm ill. No, tell her I went to the toilet.

167
00:09:01,465 --> 00:09:04,435
No, wait. Tell her I didn't come to school today.

168
00:09:05,595 --> 00:09:07,435
She can't see my face if I do this.

169
00:09:07,635 --> 00:09:09,165
I'm not here today, okay?

170
00:09:09,635 --> 00:09:10,635
Not a word.

171
00:09:16,345 --> 00:09:17,945
Get her for me.

172
00:09:20,315 --> 00:09:22,585
She's not here today.

173
00:09:22,785 --> 00:09:23,855
She went to the teachers' office.

174
00:09:24,255 --> 00:09:25,355
She went to the infirmary.

175
00:09:25,455 --> 00:09:28,055
She was in a car accident and was admitted to a hospital.

176
00:09:28,555 --> 00:09:29,995
- Tae Gyeong. - Will...

177
00:09:30,725 --> 00:09:33,095
Will you believe me if I say she transferred away?

178
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:44,175
Darn it.

179
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:45,905
My gosh.

180
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:48,145
How long do we have to do this for?

181
00:09:50,215 --> 00:09:51,815
I feel so sorry for you.

182
00:09:52,545 --> 00:09:54,884
Why do this when you can just write it in no time?

183
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,545
I don't know. She wants the platinum package,

184
00:09:56,855 --> 00:09:58,915
and I just don't have any ideas.

185
00:10:00,455 --> 00:10:02,655
Don't you think Ji Su's nothing without her hair?

186
00:10:03,855 --> 00:10:06,325
No. Is her hair nothing without that face?

187
00:10:09,265 --> 00:10:10,265
This is madness.

188
00:10:10,266 --> 00:10:12,095
Ask him out yourself.

189
00:10:13,065 --> 00:10:14,135
What?

190
00:10:14,465 --> 00:10:17,675
Why would you say that? Are you insane?

191
00:10:17,735 --> 00:10:19,074
Don't drag this out.

192
00:10:19,075 --> 00:10:21,274
Ask him out and get rejected.

193
00:10:21,275 --> 00:10:22,904
The more miserable your love life is,

194
00:10:22,905 --> 00:10:24,974
the greater stepping stone it can become.

195
00:10:24,975 --> 00:10:26,984
Singers release their greatest hits after a breakup.

196
00:10:26,985 --> 00:10:28,514
What are you talking about?

197
00:10:28,515 --> 00:10:29,585
Take that back.

198
00:10:29,985 --> 00:10:31,755
- Take it back right now. - Hee Wan!

199
00:10:33,555 --> 00:10:35,524
- Hey, the cup noodles... - Go.

200
00:10:35,525 --> 00:10:36,794
- I'll be right back. - Go, now.

201
00:10:36,795 --> 00:10:38,994
- Get out of here. - No, Hee Wan. Wait.

202
00:10:38,995 --> 00:10:41,625
- Hee Wan! Wait. - Go!

203
00:11:05,015 --> 00:11:06,015
Hey.

204
00:11:09,285 --> 00:11:10,555
She was right here.

205
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:12,625
Wait.

206
00:11:18,735 --> 00:11:19,735
Hey!

207
00:11:21,605 --> 00:11:23,435
- Let's go! - Run!

208
00:11:23,975 --> 00:11:26,075
- What the heck? - My gosh.

209
00:11:26,175 --> 00:11:27,245
Darn it.

210
00:11:28,575 --> 00:11:29,945
Hee Wan.

211
00:11:34,315 --> 00:11:35,345
Hee Wan?

212
00:11:41,555 --> 00:11:42,585
What?

213
00:11:54,005 --> 00:11:55,705
- Oh, no. - This is a habit of hers.

214
00:11:55,905 --> 00:11:57,534
- Did she really jump? - My gosh.

215
00:11:57,535 --> 00:11:59,235
- Is she okay? - What's going on?

216
00:12:01,545 --> 00:12:03,345
Hello, this is Hee Wan Tang.

217
00:12:05,145 --> 00:12:06,245
A suicide attempt?

218
00:12:06,815 --> 00:12:07,914
Dad!

219
00:12:07,915 --> 00:12:09,485
What's going on?

220
00:12:09,515 --> 00:12:12,985
She looked so cheerful and carefree the last time we met.

221
00:12:13,015 --> 00:12:14,685
She still doesn't have a worry in the world.

222
00:12:15,785 --> 00:12:17,825
- How can you say that? - I mean...

223
00:12:18,025 --> 00:12:20,725
she does weird stuff you can never imagine.

224
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:26,635
You talk as if you didn't care at all.

225
00:12:26,665 --> 00:12:27,935
People who struggle...

226
00:12:28,635 --> 00:12:31,175
pretend to be extra cheerful...

227
00:12:31,705 --> 00:12:34,605
to hide how they really feel.

228
00:12:37,975 --> 00:12:39,575
Did Ram Woo try to off herself?

229
00:12:40,115 --> 00:12:41,445
Is Ram Woo okay?

230
00:12:41,545 --> 00:12:43,415
- Is something wrong? - I don't know.

231
00:12:43,815 --> 00:12:44,885
Me neither.

232
00:12:50,025 --> 00:12:53,225
If there's anything I can do to help, tell me.

233
00:13:01,965 --> 00:13:03,935
She has lost her mind.

234
00:13:05,405 --> 00:13:06,945
I think she went insane.

235
00:13:10,215 --> 00:13:12,614
Everyone thought you were out of your mind.

236
00:13:12,615 --> 00:13:14,045
We were so worried.

237
00:13:14,785 --> 00:13:15,944
Where are we going?

238
00:13:15,945 --> 00:13:17,485
"We" are not going anywhere.

239
00:13:19,915 --> 00:13:21,655
Why am I even talking to you?

240
00:13:23,555 --> 00:13:26,024
- Accept the fact. - Darn it.

241
00:13:26,025 --> 00:13:27,264
You're not crazy.

242
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:28,994
- I'm a grim reaper. - I don't hear you.

243
00:13:28,995 --> 00:13:31,694
- I don't hear you. - She must be crazy.

244
00:13:31,695 --> 00:13:33,194
I don't.

245
00:13:33,195 --> 00:13:34,934
(Aperion Spa Land, Customer Instructions)

246
00:13:34,935 --> 00:13:36,165
- Welcome. - Hello.

247
00:13:37,135 --> 00:13:38,205
One adult, please.

248
00:13:38,835 --> 00:13:40,135
The doors are closing.

249
00:13:40,275 --> 00:13:42,205
I see you're still as smart.

250
00:14:19,675 --> 00:14:22,015
Why are you even more down after the bath?

251
00:14:24,715 --> 00:14:28,155
I feel clean and refreshed for once.

252
00:14:28,525 --> 00:14:29,784
I felt lethargic,

253
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:31,795
but the bath was a lifesaver.

254
00:14:32,555 --> 00:14:35,665
Was that a weird word to use for a dead guy?

255
00:14:38,665 --> 00:14:40,195
Let's say I'll actually die.

256
00:14:40,935 --> 00:14:43,005
Why do you have to be the one to tell me?

257
00:14:43,535 --> 00:14:44,575
Well...

258
00:14:47,645 --> 00:14:49,445
Call it a favour from a friend.

259
00:14:50,575 --> 00:14:52,345
- Let's say that's it. - A favour?

260
00:14:53,015 --> 00:14:54,915
Then get lost now. I have no use for you.

261
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:56,945
Or come back when I die.

262
00:15:03,225 --> 00:15:05,455
Hey. Why are you dragging me here?

263
00:15:07,595 --> 00:15:08,595
How long has it been?

264
00:15:08,596 --> 00:15:10,595
I did 18 times at 5-minute intervals.

265
00:15:10,995 --> 00:15:12,095
Give it to him.

266
00:15:18,475 --> 00:15:19,734
It's in.

267
00:15:19,735 --> 00:15:21,975
- As he's passing away first, - Stop. Switch with me.

268
00:15:22,105 --> 00:15:23,915
I brought her with me.

269
00:15:25,275 --> 00:15:26,975
We have a patient! Make way, please!

270
00:15:27,185 --> 00:15:28,245
Move please!

271
00:15:28,545 --> 00:15:30,215
- Get an OR room for GS. - Understood.

272
00:15:41,865 --> 00:15:42,865
What's this?

273
00:15:43,795 --> 00:15:45,495
BP is dropping. It's 40.

274
00:15:46,635 --> 00:15:47,665
Doctor.

275
00:15:52,305 --> 00:15:53,305
Let's stop.

276
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:57,115
Time of death, 4:55pm.

277
00:16:01,115 --> 00:16:02,885
Mr. Lim Su Hyeon has passed away.

278
00:16:04,585 --> 00:16:05,914
Born in the Year of the White Sheep...

279
00:16:05,915 --> 00:16:07,225
on October 6 between 11pm to 1am.

280
00:16:07,425 --> 00:16:10,355
Died in the Year of the Blue Dragon on April 1 between 3pm to 5pm.

281
00:16:11,925 --> 00:16:14,195
Lim Su Hyeon.

282
00:16:50,935 --> 00:16:51,965
Let's go.

283
00:17:01,005 --> 00:17:02,505
Has it hit you now?

284
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:09,185
You're sure, right?

285
00:17:10,015 --> 00:17:11,085
Yes.

286
00:17:12,455 --> 00:17:13,885
How do I die?

287
00:17:14,255 --> 00:17:15,785
I can't tell you.

288
00:17:17,025 --> 00:17:18,425
One week, was it?

289
00:17:20,225 --> 00:17:21,295
Yes.

290
00:17:32,075 --> 00:17:34,875
What do you want to do in your last week?

291
00:17:36,545 --> 00:17:37,975
I want to go home and sleep.

292
00:17:38,845 --> 00:17:40,315
What? Hey.

293
00:17:41,885 --> 00:17:44,585
You're going to sleep when you'll die in a week?

294
00:17:44,785 --> 00:17:46,115
What else am I to do?

295
00:17:46,515 --> 00:17:47,585
Goodness.

296
00:17:49,025 --> 00:17:50,155
Really.

297
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,395
Isn't there anything you want to do?

298
00:17:53,495 --> 00:17:56,264
Someone you wanted to meet or a place you wanted to go.

299
00:17:56,265 --> 00:17:58,164
Or food you couldn't eat because it was too expensive.

300
00:17:58,165 --> 00:17:59,194
Anything you like.

301
00:17:59,195 --> 00:18:01,404
A tour of the oldest bakeries in the country.

302
00:18:01,405 --> 00:18:03,875
How about solving a challenging math problem?

303
00:18:04,475 --> 00:18:06,405
Isn't that what you want to do?

304
00:18:10,345 --> 00:18:11,975
I have something else I want to do.

305
00:18:19,555 --> 00:18:21,225
"Riding a tandem bike?"

306
00:18:21,555 --> 00:18:23,755
"Drinking beer while looking at the night view."

307
00:18:24,655 --> 00:18:25,725
What are these?

308
00:18:26,295 --> 00:18:27,695
My bucket list.

309
00:18:27,965 --> 00:18:30,535
Isn't a bucket list something you do before you die?

310
00:18:30,835 --> 00:18:31,895
I'm...

311
00:18:32,695 --> 00:18:33,935
indeed already dead.

312
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:37,935
Do them with me.

313
00:18:41,745 --> 00:18:43,914
- You must keep your balance. - It's dangerous.

314
00:18:43,915 --> 00:18:45,714
You're the one moving around, making it sway.

315
00:18:45,715 --> 00:18:47,444
- I didn't do anything. - I'm moving straight.

316
00:18:47,445 --> 00:18:50,044
We're too fast. You have to keep the balance.

317
00:18:50,045 --> 00:18:51,954
Or else the bicycle keeps swaying.

318
00:18:51,955 --> 00:18:52,955
Be careful.

319
00:18:52,956 --> 00:18:54,925
What is wrong with you?

320
00:18:55,225 --> 00:18:56,285
I don't want to.

321
00:18:56,655 --> 00:18:57,825
You can do them alone.

322
00:18:59,495 --> 00:19:01,025
Is this really too much to ask?

323
00:19:04,895 --> 00:19:06,065
You know, between us.

324
00:19:12,405 --> 00:19:15,274
Hey. I've been looking for you for ages.

325
00:19:15,275 --> 00:19:18,175
I wonder why we missed each other so much.

326
00:19:18,575 --> 00:19:20,714
Why are you doing this to me?

327
00:19:20,715 --> 00:19:22,584
Isn't this obvious?

328
00:19:22,585 --> 00:19:25,014
Since this is platinum,

329
00:19:25,015 --> 00:19:26,015
I have a grave responsibility.

330
00:19:26,016 --> 00:19:28,284
I really want things to work out between you and Ram Woo.

331
00:19:28,285 --> 00:19:29,924
I'm working super hard...

332
00:19:29,925 --> 00:19:31,394
- Right. - and being extra careful.

333
00:19:31,395 --> 00:19:32,825
What about my letter?

334
00:19:32,955 --> 00:19:34,295
Is it not ready yet?

335
00:19:34,695 --> 00:19:35,765
Not yet?

336
00:19:37,095 --> 00:19:38,265
But I'm almost there.

337
00:19:38,465 --> 00:19:40,534
One percent is all that's left.

338
00:19:40,535 --> 00:19:42,904
In hopes things work out for you two,

339
00:19:42,905 --> 00:19:44,904
I've been throwing my heart and soul into it that I...

340
00:19:44,905 --> 00:19:47,504
Hee Wan. Do you have feelings...

341
00:19:47,505 --> 00:19:50,375
for Hee Wan... No, Ram Woo?

342
00:19:52,645 --> 00:19:53,645
What?

343
00:19:56,885 --> 00:19:59,755
What kind of nonsense are you spouting?

344
00:19:59,815 --> 00:20:01,854
Pretty girls have...

345
00:20:01,855 --> 00:20:04,124
the silliest imaginations at times.

346
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:05,654
Right, Tae Gyeong?

347
00:20:05,655 --> 00:20:07,494
Yes. Ram Woo and Hee Wan?

348
00:20:07,495 --> 00:20:09,495
- You're making me sick. - Gosh.

349
00:20:09,995 --> 00:20:12,765
Oh, no. Are you okay? I also feel like throwing up.

350
00:20:13,135 --> 00:20:14,604
- I see. - I feel sick.

351
00:20:14,605 --> 00:20:17,805
How you act makes it more suspicious.

352
00:20:21,075 --> 00:20:24,614
No way. I swear that...

353
00:20:24,615 --> 00:20:26,014
I hate him, okay?

354
00:20:26,015 --> 00:20:28,514
He's the type I hate. Get it?

355
00:20:28,515 --> 00:20:30,514
But how can you not like him?

356
00:20:30,515 --> 00:20:32,754
He's tall with broad shoulders.

357
00:20:32,755 --> 00:20:33,784
And his face is tiny.

358
00:20:33,785 --> 00:20:35,524
She has a herniated disc and hates tall men.

359
00:20:35,525 --> 00:20:36,724
She's right.

360
00:20:36,725 --> 00:20:39,194
Even besides those, when he smiles,

361
00:20:39,195 --> 00:20:40,325
his eyes look like a half-moon.

362
00:20:40,895 --> 00:20:42,024
That's adorable.

363
00:20:42,025 --> 00:20:43,624
No, I hate it.

364
00:20:43,625 --> 00:20:45,194
- I loathe that type. - She...

365
00:20:45,195 --> 00:20:46,964
I hate it when men smile.

366
00:20:46,965 --> 00:20:49,035
This girl loves trashy guys.

367
00:20:50,265 --> 00:20:52,104
My bad.

368
00:20:52,105 --> 00:20:55,374
Since Ram Woo is such a nice guy,

369
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:57,304
I thought some might not know their place...

370
00:20:57,305 --> 00:20:59,075
and try to hit on him.

371
00:20:59,575 --> 00:21:01,785
I'm sorry for getting the wrong idea.

372
00:21:02,015 --> 00:21:04,755
Right. You better apologize.

373
00:21:05,385 --> 00:21:07,155
I'm glad it's a misunderstanding.

374
00:21:07,255 --> 00:21:09,024
I'll take the letter now.

375
00:21:09,025 --> 00:21:10,185
It's in your classroom, right?

376
00:21:10,755 --> 00:21:11,825
What?

377
00:21:13,025 --> 00:21:15,524
Come on, Hee Wan. The letter.

378
00:21:15,525 --> 00:21:17,194
You said only one percent was left.

379
00:21:17,195 --> 00:21:18,935
Can't you finish it off right now?

380
00:21:50,695 --> 00:21:54,264
It's in a dead serious font, Hee Wan.

381
00:21:54,265 --> 00:21:55,805
(Dear Kim Ram Woo)

382
00:21:55,965 --> 00:21:57,035
Yes.

383
00:21:57,305 --> 00:21:59,174
Since the content is so passionate,

384
00:21:59,175 --> 00:22:01,844
I think the decoration should be minimal.

385
00:22:01,845 --> 00:22:04,714
Oh, I see.

386
00:22:04,715 --> 00:22:07,115
And the remaining one percent?

387
00:22:07,375 --> 00:22:08,845
What's there to do?

388
00:22:44,385 --> 00:22:45,385
A poop colour?

389
00:22:49,325 --> 00:22:51,224
Ram Woo must like...

390
00:22:51,225 --> 00:22:54,565
the colour brown, right?

391
00:22:57,595 --> 00:22:59,295
(Sincerely, Bang Ji Su)

392
00:22:59,465 --> 00:23:01,765
It's 100 percent complete.

393
00:23:03,005 --> 00:23:04,775
Thank you!

394
00:23:15,815 --> 00:23:18,685
A night view is so not the vibe.

395
00:23:19,355 --> 00:23:21,554
And why the tandem bike of all things?

396
00:23:21,555 --> 00:23:23,484
If it was a regular bike, I had to ride behind you.

397
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:26,495
Whatever. Just strike out what we just did earlier.

398
00:23:28,025 --> 00:23:30,124
Done with riding a tandem bike.

399
00:23:30,125 --> 00:23:31,295
What's left to do is...

400
00:23:31,495 --> 00:23:33,394
bird watching at a migratory bird sanctuary,

401
00:23:33,395 --> 00:23:35,534
watching a classical performance at the Seoul Arts Center,

402
00:23:35,535 --> 00:23:37,734
eating ramyeon in the Arctic, backpacking through South America,

403
00:23:37,735 --> 00:23:39,375
- and going on "National Singing..." - What?

404
00:23:40,505 --> 00:23:43,105
What are all of these? "Buying a house."

405
00:23:43,475 --> 00:23:45,645
"Giving pocket money to my grandchildren."

406
00:23:47,915 --> 00:23:49,644
Are you kidding me?

407
00:23:49,645 --> 00:23:52,114
How can I make grandchildren right here, right now?

408
00:23:52,115 --> 00:23:53,255
Come on.

409
00:23:54,155 --> 00:23:56,224
The bucket list doesn't always...

410
00:23:56,225 --> 00:23:57,755
have to be realistic.

411
00:23:58,025 --> 00:24:00,095
Those are things I want to do before I die.

412
00:24:01,225 --> 00:24:02,295
Right.

413
00:24:02,425 --> 00:24:04,865
If not, that won't be a bucket list. No.

414
00:24:05,165 --> 00:24:06,795
Isn't that miserable?

415
00:24:07,835 --> 00:24:09,864
Going around alone as a grim reaper...

416
00:24:09,865 --> 00:24:11,305
is no fun.

417
00:24:23,315 --> 00:24:26,115
Only 10, okay? 10.

418
00:24:27,415 --> 00:24:29,555
You can do that for me, no?

419
00:24:30,585 --> 00:24:33,025
Will you leave after we do ten?

420
00:24:35,325 --> 00:24:36,425
What?

421
00:24:36,565 --> 00:24:37,695
Promise me.

422
00:24:38,795 --> 00:24:40,664
That you'll leave me after we're done...

423
00:24:40,665 --> 00:24:41,935
and won't come see me again.

424
00:24:45,575 --> 00:24:46,605
Okay.

425
00:24:48,245 --> 00:24:50,245
Do those, and it'll be the end.

426
00:24:52,545 --> 00:24:54,684
I'll disappear from your sight right away.

427
00:24:54,685 --> 00:24:55,745
All right?

428
00:24:59,485 --> 00:25:02,725
By the way, isn't the night view here amazing?

429
00:25:06,025 --> 00:25:08,465
You have such a cliche taste.

430
00:25:10,425 --> 00:25:12,094
Are you done here?

431
00:25:12,095 --> 00:25:14,065
If so, let's move on to the next one.

432
00:25:15,065 --> 00:25:17,004
You are really stingy.

433
00:25:17,005 --> 00:25:18,875
Let's go do the next thing on the list.

434
00:25:19,175 --> 00:25:21,604
Come on, Kim Ram Woo.

435
00:25:21,605 --> 00:25:22,844
What a strange girl.

436
00:25:22,845 --> 00:25:25,545
We have to take the bike with us.

437
00:25:34,015 --> 00:25:37,485
(Bird watching at a migratory bird sanctuary)

438
00:25:37,525 --> 00:25:38,555
(Bird watching)

439
00:25:48,305 --> 00:25:51,934
