444
00:26:13,695 --> 00:26:14,724
(Watching a classical performance)

445
00:26:14,725 --> 00:26:16,465
Hey. Wake me up after the show.

446
00:26:17,595 --> 00:26:18,735
Mind your manners.

447
00:26:43,285 --> 00:26:44,794
I did some thinking.

448
00:26:44,795 --> 00:26:47,355
Friends are better than boyfriends.

449
00:26:48,165 --> 00:26:49,394
It's about Jung Hee Wan, right?

450
00:26:49,395 --> 00:26:51,894
Honestly, how long would high school relationships last?

451
00:26:51,895 --> 00:26:54,035
It's over when he graduates and goes to college.

452
00:26:54,165 --> 00:26:56,264
He'll find a new girlfriend in college.

453
00:26:56,265 --> 00:26:58,234
But it'll be over when he goes to the military.

454
00:26:58,235 --> 00:26:59,834
He'll find another one after being discharged.

455
00:26:59,835 --> 00:27:02,545
But again, he'll break up after finding a job.

456
00:27:03,005 --> 00:27:04,444
It's an endless cycle.

457
00:27:04,445 --> 00:27:05,775
But friends are different.

458
00:27:06,275 --> 00:27:08,884
In the long run, who's the real winner?

459
00:27:08,885 --> 00:27:11,314
- Friends. - It sounds like self-justification,

460
00:27:11,315 --> 00:27:12,685
but you have a point.

461
00:27:12,985 --> 00:27:14,424
Frankly, dating is a pain.

462
00:27:14,425 --> 00:27:16,184
You have to celebrate 100 days, 200 days,

463
00:27:16,185 --> 00:27:18,424
- and his birthday. - Also Pepero Day.

464
00:27:18,425 --> 00:27:20,024
You can't miss Christmas.

465
00:27:20,025 --> 00:27:21,594
Not to mention, summer means sweaty hands.

466
00:27:21,595 --> 00:27:22,794
But you still have to hold hands.

467
00:27:22,795 --> 00:27:24,895
- I hate it. - It makes me sick.

468
00:27:24,965 --> 00:27:26,564
That's why I'm telling you that...

469
00:27:26,565 --> 00:27:29,504
Jung Hee Wan and Bang Ji Su won't last long.

470
00:27:29,505 --> 00:27:31,904
In the end, who's the winner?

471
00:27:31,905 --> 00:27:33,534
Me, who hasn't confessed to him.

472
00:27:33,535 --> 00:27:35,045
There goes Ji Su and Jung Hee Wan.

473
00:27:36,775 --> 00:27:40,414
Gosh, there's this warm filter around them.

474
00:27:40,415 --> 00:27:41,685
I bet she'll confess to him.

475
00:27:45,955 --> 00:27:47,054
Jung Hee Wan is smiling,

476
00:27:47,055 --> 00:27:48,955
making that half-moon sort of eyes.

477
00:27:51,195 --> 00:27:53,725
But like you said, I'm sure they'll break up soon.

478
00:27:58,735 --> 00:28:00,035
Hey! Your crutch!

479
00:28:04,205 --> 00:28:06,335
- Is she okay? - What are you doing?

480
00:28:13,815 --> 00:28:15,415
Move it!

481
00:28:37,665 --> 00:28:38,935
No!

482
00:28:44,245 --> 00:28:45,415
What's wrong with her?

483
00:28:46,415 --> 00:28:47,745
- Is she dead? - What?

484
00:28:49,545 --> 00:28:50,545
Hee Wan?

485
00:28:51,685 --> 00:28:54,255
- Is your leg okay? - Is she okay?

486
00:28:54,655 --> 00:28:55,725
Oh, no.

487
00:28:55,985 --> 00:28:56,985
What...

488
00:28:58,755 --> 00:29:00,755
- Guys. Let's keep playing. - She looks okay.

489
00:29:01,165 --> 00:29:02,695
Where's your crutch?

490
00:29:03,725 --> 00:29:04,895
Are you really okay?

491
00:29:07,665 --> 00:29:09,005
Hee Wan?

492
00:29:09,465 --> 00:29:12,074
What was the "no" about?

493
00:29:12,075 --> 00:29:13,075
What?

494
00:29:13,875 --> 00:29:17,005
You see...

495
00:29:18,375 --> 00:29:19,445
Well...

496
00:29:23,145 --> 00:29:24,984
I like you, Kim Ram Woo.

497
00:29:24,985 --> 00:29:27,315
(1: Confess my true feelings to Ram Woo.)

498
00:29:29,185 --> 00:29:30,255
What?

499
00:29:33,595 --> 00:29:36,025
I'm sorry, but I like Ji Su.

500
00:29:36,865 --> 00:29:38,664
It's awkward to be friends now.

501
00:29:38,665 --> 00:29:40,265
Let's act like strangers.

502
00:29:44,905 --> 00:29:45,905
No.

503
00:29:46,475 --> 00:29:47,945
(1: Confess my true feelings to Ram Woo.)

504
00:29:51,515 --> 00:29:53,515
I like you, Ji Su.

505
00:29:54,415 --> 00:29:55,684
I can't give her to you.

506
00:29:55,685 --> 00:29:57,315
(2: Act like I like Ji Su.)

507
00:29:57,645 --> 00:29:59,085
I see.

508
00:29:59,855 --> 00:30:01,724
I hope things work out for you two.

509
00:30:01,725 --> 00:30:03,025
My gosh, Hee Wan.

510
00:30:04,025 --> 00:30:06,394
Was that why you've been...

511
00:30:06,395 --> 00:30:09,325
Then we'll stay friends for the rest of our lives, right?

512
00:30:11,265 --> 00:30:13,135
No.

513
00:30:14,265 --> 00:30:17,034
My gosh, Hee Wan. You saved me from embarrassing myself.

514
00:30:17,035 --> 00:30:19,504
You're my lifesaver. I mean it.

515
00:30:19,505 --> 00:30:20,775
(3: Tell Ji Su that there's a chilli flake between her teeth.)

516
00:30:21,305 --> 00:30:22,305
My gosh.

517
00:30:22,306 --> 00:30:24,405
I don't care if there's spinach stuck between your teeth.

518
00:30:24,875 --> 00:30:25,945
You still look beautiful.

519
00:30:29,045 --> 00:30:30,085
No.

520
00:30:31,215 --> 00:30:32,385
Are you kidding me?

521
00:30:32,555 --> 00:30:34,214
If you start dating, you won't have time to play board games with me.

522
00:30:34,215 --> 00:30:35,825
(4: Tell him he can't date her because Hong Seok will be lonely.)

523
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:38,825
I'm sorry about that.

524
00:30:39,025 --> 00:30:40,525
You can play board games with Ram Woo from now on.

525
00:30:42,025 --> 00:30:43,025
What?

526
00:30:49,405 --> 00:30:50,435
This is not it!

527
00:30:51,935 --> 00:30:54,604
My gosh, what's going on? There's romance in the air.

528
00:30:54,605 --> 00:30:55,944
It's making me cringe hardcore.

529
00:30:55,945 --> 00:30:57,574
So I needed an eyepatch like a hardcore pirate.

530
00:30:57,575 --> 00:30:58,874
I can't watch this, so I need an eyepatch.

531
00:30:58,875 --> 00:31:00,515
I'd rather cover up my eyes and not watch this.

532
00:31:00,545 --> 00:31:02,615
An eyepatch to cover up my eyes.

533
00:31:02,785 --> 00:31:04,715
(99: Tell them I was looking for an eyepatch.)

534
00:31:07,815 --> 00:31:08,855
Hee Wan.

535
00:31:09,185 --> 00:31:11,355
No matter how hard I try to make sense of this,

536
00:31:11,495 --> 00:31:13,655
- this makes no sense. - This makes no sense.

537
00:31:15,295 --> 00:31:17,365
- Hee Wan? - Well...

538
00:31:19,795 --> 00:31:20,834
I...

539
00:31:20,835 --> 00:31:23,605
Please say something.

540
00:31:23,765 --> 00:31:25,605
Well, the truth is...

541
00:31:30,605 --> 00:31:32,015
(Bang Ji Su)

542
00:31:32,345 --> 00:31:33,475
Kim Ram Woo!

543
00:31:38,585 --> 00:31:39,615
Ma'am!

544
00:31:43,855 --> 00:31:44,924
She got hit in the head.

545
00:31:44,925 --> 00:31:46,894
She recently jumped off the restroom window.

546
00:31:46,895 --> 00:31:49,795
And I don't know what happened to her.

547
00:31:50,025 --> 00:31:51,494
She's been acting weird.

